1. Motion Sickness
I believe Oculus is responsible for this problem. I tried many VR games and I could only bear the "moving by jump" style, like ALYX (default). The MOH: Above & Beyond made me sick. After many hours playing I could bear only 30 minutes playing. BUT one day I found myself never feel sick again. My friend had similar problem in DCS: World and he had a same conclusion about this. In some day of 2021 they must upgraded VR system and you'll find that all complaints about motion sickness (not only about this game) is in first half of 2021 or earlier.

2. Protect Controller (and monitor)
I had a plan for this. At first I found a "Golden point" that I could stretch out my arms without hit anything. But I still hit my wardrobe for twice. I found myself displaced from my "Golden point". My solution is playing the game just beside my bed. I can wave my arms above my bed. And I keep brace myself on my bedside by calf muscles. Then I can return my position and direction easily even after a bloody fighting.

